comment:
* Information exposed to {@link android.app.InstantAppResolverService} to complete
 * an instant application resolution request.
 * @hide

variables.name: mIntent
variables.comment:
* The sanitized {@link Intent} used for resolution. A sanitized Intent is an intent with
     * potential PII removed from the original intent. Fields removed include extras and the
     * host + path of the data, if defined.

variables.name: mHostDigestPrefix
variables.comment: The hash prefix of the instant app's domain or null if no host is defined.

variables.name: mUserHandle
variables.comment: The user requesting the instant application

variables.name: mRequesterInstantApp
variables.comment: Whether or not the requesting package was an instant app itself

methods.name: public Intent getIntent()
